<br>
Dark Age of Camelot <br>
<br>
version 1.53c Test Release Notes <br>
<br>
================================ <br>
<br>
<br>
NEW THINGS AND BUG FIXES <br>
<br>
- You can now highlight an item in a store and click &quot;buy&quot; multiple times to buy multiple items. <br>
<br>
- Fixed the weird clipping plane problems in dungeons (especially Darkness Falls). This fixes a Pendragon-only bug. <br>
<br>
- The middle button can once again be configured in the keyboard configuration. <br>
<br>
- When you clicked BUY twice at a store, it would print an odd error message or sometimes attempt to purchase a random item if the store had multiple pages. This has been fixed. <br>
<br>
- Gold should now update correctly when trading to another player. Start a trade, then change the amount of money in your trade window. It should correctly update to the other player. <br>
<br>
- &quot;making change&quot; in the trade window should work correctly. Try to trade a single gold to another player. Then try to &quot;pull back&quot; 20 or so silver. You should no longer see 1G -20S on the screen - it should make correct change. <br>
<br>
- All held equipment (weapons, shields, helms, etc) should now be &quot;lodded&quot; (removed) from the figure at a distance of 2500 units. This should help alleviate some of the frame rate problems that occur when many players are on screen at the same time. <br>
<br>
- When you delve your weapons, the correct base and clamped DPS are printed - they were reversed. <br>
<br>
<br>
FRONTIER KEEP/RVR SYSTEM UPDATES <br>
<br>
- When your guild owns an outpost and a guard is slain at your outpost, you now receive a print via guildchat channel. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
SPELLCRAFT/ALCHEMY STUFF <br>
<br>
- Gems and Tinctures now show their quality in the lower right quick-delve window. <br>
<br>
- Fixed several bugs with the spellcrafting combine feature that resulted in wacky point amounts. <br>
<br>
- Timers are now set to a minimum of 1 second for Spellcraft and Alchemy. <br>
<br>
- Vapor Evocation Sigil icon changed to purple - its correct color. <br>
<br>
- Added Focus Gem recipes for all three realms. <br>
<br>
- Added giant blood and mystic energy to the Spellcraft Merchants. <br>
<br>
- The Airy, Dusty, and Earthen Shielding gem recipes have been re-labeled for the correct gem that they make. <br>
<br>
- Changed the name of the meadowseet ingredient to meadowsweet. <br>
<br>
- Changed the name of the Fire Shielding Jewel to the Fiery Shielding Jewel. <br>
<br>
- Changed the name of the Fire Shielding Jewel recipe to Fiery Shielding Jewel. <br>
<br>
- Added ability for tinctures to be combined onto items correctly. <br>
<br>
<br>
WORLD NOTES <br>
<br>
Hibernia - Bri Leith - Fagan has ordered his forces to scout and report back on the activities in the Cursed Forest. To support this mission, a new town with a bindstone, Brynach, has been established in the valley of Bri Leith. <br>
<br>
Quests- General: A small number of &quot;bounty&quot; quest objects have had their &quot;no sell&quot; flags removed, so that even after you’ve completed the quests the maximum number of times the drops can be sold to a merchant. These items include Fell, Dangerous, and Malefic teeth, and soul gems, sett pelts and white pelts. Be careful that you don’t sell them before you’ve maxed the quest out, as they won’t be reimbursed to you. <br>
<br>
Albion Quests: (Secret Orders): The Arawn Commander will now only appear for players on the correct step of this quest. <br>
<br>
Dungeon: Most of the boss encounters in the new dungeons have been slightly tweaked. In most cases, they have been increased in difficulty. <br>
<br>
Monsters: Albion : The Green Knight encounter has been modified to be of like difficulty to that of the Glacier Giant. <br>
<br>
Hibernia (Breifine): The Evern encounter has been modified to be of like difficulty to that of the Glacier Giant. <br>
<br>
<br>
Item notes: <br>
<br>
- The &quot;bloodless wolfhound hide&quot; and the &quot;pristine bloodless wolfhound hide&quot; should now have a sell value. <br>
<br>
- The Bitten Staff (Albion) now buffs body resist. <br>
<br>
- Beliathan's loot table has been reduced. Under some circumstances, this encounter was too easy, and the reward far outweighed the risk. In the future, we will expand the Beliathan encounter and the appropriate rewards.  <p>Angabliss - Cieix - Angha - Blademaster Team Lead<BR>
